{"schema_version":"1","crate":"wikiada","version":"1.5.0","id":"0594433bc6fbf621","name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Maps","qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Maps","kind":"ada_package","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/base/beans/util-beans-objects-maps.ads","line":40,"column":9},"code":"package Util.Beans.Objects.Maps","documentation":{"description":"== Object maps ==\nThe `Util.Beans.Objects.Maps` package provides a map of objects with a `String`\nas key.  This allows to associated names to objects.\nTo create an instance of the map, it is possible to use the `Create` function\nas follows:\n\n  with Util.Beans.Objects.Maps;\n  ...\n     Person : Util.Beans.Objects.Object := Util.Beans.Objects.Maps.Create;\n\nThen, it becomes possible to populate the map with objects by using\nthe `Set_Value` procedure as follows:\n\n  Util.Beans.Objects.Set_Value (Person, \"name\",\n                                To_Object (Name));\n  Util.Beans.Objects.Set_Value (Person, \"last_name\",\n                                To_Object (Last_Name));\n  Util.Beans.Objects.Set_Value (Person, \"age\",\n                                To_Object (Age));\n\nGetting a value from the map is done by using the `Get_Value` function:\n\n  Name : Util.Beans.Objects.Object := Get_Value (Person, \"name\");\n\nIt is also possible to iterate over the values of the map by using\nthe `Iterate` procedure or by using the iterator support provided by\nthe `Util.Beans.Objects.Iterators` package."},"tagged_types":[{"id":"c67540e5ff216b37","name":"Map_Bean","qualified_name":"Util.Beans.Objects.Maps.Map_Bean","kind":"ada_tagged_type","location":{"file":"../../../home/runner/.local/share/alire/builds/utilada_2.8.2_30b22a59/4ad568c8d185b13a4b0f496912d263f14b692e0709f1ccf771a1531595b64c8f/src/base/beans/util-beans-objects-maps.ads","line":84,"column":9},"code":"type Map_Bean is new Maps.Map and Uti